return ['messages'=>['0e1ba0e0ea5e1a671bdb6c0f20f3afba'=>'“Being someone” is.','2d2a2b70d7edb0598bf5c39afb41cf24'=>'A change in social status, since in Panama, having such a small population and a rather closed culture, it was very “easy” for me to become “someone” in that country. Someone who was even stopped on the street to ask to take photos (I\'m not saying this to brag, I usually left work looking the worst and with the worst face possible, but I mention it to give my point some perspective).','311b9279f86578dfa1d60fb6aac67473'=>'However, I feel that I have achieved a lot in the short time I have been living here. Getting to live off what I love and dedicate myself to this every day of my life (something I was never able to do in Panama).','32029970fee280339ee1cbc74603e7eb'=>'However, when I arrived in Barcelona (which was totally something I expected), instead of standing out, I was just one more of the crowd.','4607ad752c90746af1e75af150d13fc8'=>'What I mean by this is that “being someone” is not a way of living. And I can empathize with those people who do not leave the place where they are, even if they do not have a quality of life, because they know that the moment they leave, they will have to start from scratch and face the harsh reality that they are nobody outside there.','4823a3723682cbc0c1317a7b7850b2a1'=>'Don\'t be afraid to step out of your comfort zone. ','4dd41faca74bc87c6a74a77ba7cc574a'=>'From my perspective, it doesn\'t matter who you are or what you think you are where you are, if you don\'t have peace, if you don\'t have calm, it\'s not worth staying.','4f1546ba620b80004b131569b40a34f1'=>'There, being a girl, a photographer, a model, who takes nude photos, talks openly about sexuality, is tattooed, has shaved hair and I don\'t know what else... all that made me attract a lot of attention wherever I went. ','5366e1fc086fc3a0f86ec490d03f6fa1'=>'I don\'t think it was demoralizing, but I did notice a change, especially when it came to socializing and making my way in the art world.','640ffc60090cc16a218a4d70358a9901'=>'I have never been as happy as I am since I arrived in Barcelona. I have never felt so free, so myself, so at peace, with so many incredible opportunities to dedicate myself to what I love, meeting people so different and similar to me from whom I can learn.','7bcff8e48403fecfa32c9ccb09095c5f'=>'There is something I have to admit, and that is that I have noticed the change since I left Panama and started living in Barcelona.','<strong>*inserte ruido de cristal rompiéndose</strong>*'=>'<strong>*insert sound of glass breaking*</strong>','Además de que, el hecho de que hayan (en este caso) artistas mucho mejores que tú, no debería ser algo que te desmotive, sino todo lo contrario, es una inspiración y además, si consigues llegar a trabajar con esas personas, te serán de escalón para seguir subiendo a donde quieras llegar.'=>'Besides, the fact that there are (in this case) much better artists than you, shouldn\'t be something that discourages you, but on the contrary, it is an inspiration and also, if you manage to work with these people, they will be a stepping stone for you to continue climbing to where you want to go.','Allí, al ser una chica, fotógrafa, modelo, que hace fotos de desnudo, habla sobre sexualidad abiertamente, está tatuada, tiene el cabello rapado y no sé qué más… todo eso me hacía llamar mucho la atención fuese a donde fuese. '=>'There, being a girl, a photographer, a model, who takes nude photos, talks openly about sexuality, is tattooed, has shaved hair and I don\'t know what else... all that made me attract a lot of attention wherever I went. ','Bien es verdad que <em>yo no comía de eso,</em> pero se notaba.'=>'It\'s true that I didn\'t <em>eat from that stuff</em>, but it was noticeable.','Cambio con respecto al "status" social,  ya que en Panamá, al tener una población tan pequeña y tener una cultura bastante cerrada, para mí fue muy “fácil” llegar a "ser alguien" en ese país. Alguien a quien incluso paraban por la calle para pedir sacarse fotos (no lo digo por alardear, normalmente iba saliendo del trabajo con la peor pinta y la peor cara posible, pero lo menciono para dar perspectiva a mi punto).'=>'A change in social status, since in Panama, having such a small population and a rather closed culture, it was very “easy” for me to become “someone” in that country. Someone who was even stopped on the street to ask to take photos (I\'m not saying this to brag, I usually left work looking the worst and with the worst face possible, but I mention it to give my point some perspective).','Considero que no fue algo desmoralizante, pero sí se notó el cambio, sobre todo a la hora de socializar y de abrirme paso en el mundo del arte.'=>'I don\'t think it was demoralizing, but I did notice a change, especially when it came to socializing and making my way in the art world.','Desde mi perspectiva, no importa quién seas o creas que eres donde estás, sino tienes paz, sino tienes calma, no vale la pena quedarse.'=>'From my perspective, it doesn\'t matter who you are or what you think you are where you are, if you don\'t have peace, if you don\'t have calm, it\'s not worth staying.','El bienestar no es negociable.'=>'Wellbeing is non-negotiable.','El “ser alguien” sí que lo es.'=>'“Being someone” is.','En cambio, al llegar a Barcelona (totalmente era algo que me esperaba), en lugar de resaltar, era una más del montón.'=>'However, when I arrived in Barcelona (which was totally something I expected), instead of standing out, I was just one more of the crowd.','Fotógrafas hay muchísimas y mucho mejores que yo. Que hagan fotografía de desnudo, hay por montones. Divulgadoras sobre sexualidad. Gente con tatuajes y vestimentas impresionantes, chicas con el cabello de todas las formas posibles. Personas no-monogamas hay demasiadas y cada vez más… aquí yo no soy nadie especial, solo una inmigrante más.'=>'There are many female photographers, much better than me. There are plenty of them who do nude photography. Sexuality educators. People with tattoos and impressive clothes, girls with their hair in every possible way. There are too many non-monogamous people and more and more of them… I am nobody special here, just another immigrant.','Hay algo que tengo que admitir, y es que que he notado el cambio al de irme de Panamá y empezar a vivir en Barcelona.'=>'There is something I have to admit, and that is that I have noticed the change since I left Panama and started living in Barcelona.','Lo que quiero decir con esto es que, de “ser alguien” no se vive. Y que puedo llegar a empatizar con aquellas personas que no se van del lugar de donde están, aunque no tengan calidad de vida, porque saben que en el momento que se vayan, tendrán que empezar de cero y enfrentarse a la cruda realidad de que no son nadie fuera de allí.'=>'What I mean by this is that “being someone” is not a way of living. And I can empathize with those people who do not leave the place where they are, even if they do not have a quality of life, because they know that the moment they leave, they will have to start from scratch and face the harsh reality that they are nobody outside there.','Mi punto es que no tengas miedo a cambiar, no tengas miedo a perder esa posición ficticia que sientes que tienes dentro de tu micro-sociedad. Si cuentas con una calidad de vida que te permita estar tranquilx, sin preguntarte si tendrás para comer mañana o si te robarán el móvil cada vez que sales a la calle, te garantizo que si te priorizas, tendrás el tiempo para dedicarte a hacer crecer tu marca personal, vayas donde vayas. Y si eres genuino, constante y crees en ti y en lo que haces, eso se notará estés donde estés.'=>'My point is, don\'t be afraid to change, don\'t be afraid to lose that fictitious position that you feel you have within your micro-society. If you have a quality of life that allows you to be calm, without wondering if you will have something to eat tomorrow or if your phone will be stolen every time you go out, I guarantee that if you prioritize yourself, you will have the time to dedicate yourself to growing your personal brand, wherever you go. And if you are genuine, consistent and believe in yourself and what you do, it will show wherever you are.','No tengas miedo a perder tu status.'=>'Don\'t be afraid of losing your status.','No tengas miedo a salir de tu zona de confort. '=>'Don\'t be afraid to step out of your comfort zone. ','Salir de su fantasía.'=>'Get out of your fantasy.','Sin embargo, considero que he logrado muchísimo para el poco tiempo que tengo viviendo acá. Llegando a vivir de lo que amo y dedicarme a esto cada día de mi vida (cosa que nunca pude hacer en Panamá).'=>'However, I feel that I have achieved a lot in the short time I have been living here. Getting to live off what I love and dedicate myself to this every day of my life (something I was never able to do in Panama).','Yo nunca había sido tan feliz como lo soy desde que llegué a Barcelona, nunca me había sentido tan libre, tan yo, tan en paz, con tantas oportunidades increíbles de dedicarme a lo que amo, encontrando a personas tan diferentes y parecidas a mí de quienes poder aprender.'=>'I have never been as happy as I am since I arrived in Barcelona. I have never felt so free, so myself, so at peace, with so many incredible opportunities to dedicate myself to what I love, meeting people so different and similar to me from whom I can learn.','aa1a9f107c8359dc9b06269104d2510b'=>'It\'s true that I didn\'t <em>eat from that stuff</em>, but it was noticeable.','b03fc42c1a8b619c6e81e59130ef6feb'=>'Wellbeing is non-negotiable.','b58d8ec30d9d149900765a9aa3fa65ca'=>'Don\'t be afraid of losing your status.','c174f949ae5033e859246603cccb284e'=>'Get out of your fantasy.','ed2578e8b50433cd64ce9932abc0863b'=>'My point is, don\'t be afraid to change, don\'t be afraid to lose that fictitious position that you feel you have within your micro-society. If you have a quality of life that allows you to be calm, without wondering if you will have something to eat tomorrow or if your phone will be stolen every time you go out, I guarantee that if you prioritize yourself, you will have the time to dedicate yourself to growing your personal brand, wherever you go. And if you are genuine, consistent and believe in yourself and what you do, it will show wherever you are.','fb89fff8f778d13860ea119630218ee5'=>'Besides, the fact that there are (in this case) much better artists than you, shouldn\'t be something that discourages you, but on the contrary, it is an inspiration and also, if you manage to work with these people, they will be a stepping stone for you to continue climbing to where you want to go.','fd5c59aa9af455db2513a82344bc9955'=>'<strong>*insert sound of glass breaking*</strong>','ff29431465f204453c281f3398cea954'=>'There are many female photographers, much better than me. There are plenty of them who do nude photography. Sexuality educators. People with tattoos and impressive clothes, girls with their hair in every possible way. There are too many non-monogamous people and more and more of them… I am nobody special here, just another immigrant.']];
